            "content": "Solar panels require minimal ongoing maintenance with no moving parts needing regular service. Casas Adobes' desert climate presents specific considerations but proper care requires minimal time and expense. Panel cleaning: Desert dust accumulation reduces production 3-8% depending on severity. Clean 2-3 times yearly for optimal performance: Late October after monsoon season ends, early March before peak summer production season, mid-July during monsoon if heavy dust storms occur. Use standard garden hose with spray nozzle in early morning or evening avoiding thermal shock from cold water on hot panels (don't clean during mid-day heat). No pressure washers or abrasive cleaning agents. Let water sheet off naturally without wiping. Most homeowners handle cleaning in 20-30 minutes. Professional cleaning services available: $95-$145 depending on roof height and system size. Vegetation management: Trim trees and shrubs semi-annually ensuring no shade falls on panels between 9am-3pm during any season. Even partial shading from small branches dramatically reduces output. Casas Adobes' mature landscaping requires vigilant monitoring as desert trees grow continuously. Monitoring: Check smartphone app weekly verifying production appears normal for current weather and season. Sudden drops exceeding 20% warrant investigation for inverter malfunction, electrical issues, utility problems, or heavy soiling. Professional inspections: Comprehensive system inspections every 3-5 years ($145-$195) include electrical connection tightness verification, inverter operation testing, panel condition assessment, racking and mounting integrity checks, grounding system verification. Catch small issues before expensive problems develop. Properly maintained systems exceed 30-year operational lifespans with degradation under 15% over three decades."
